## Testing layout

| Directory | Purpose | Rules |
|---|---|---|
| `tests/fixtures/` | Deterministic IDs, emails, copy strings, static factories | No Playwright/browser APIs; no ERP workflows; parity enforced by `pnpm lint:fixtures-parity` |
| `tests/unit/` | Vitest — **projects** `unit-pure` (`isolate: false`) · `unit-node` · `unit-dom` (`happy-dom`) | Zod/schema-only: **`*.pure.test.ts`**. DOM/RTL: **`*.dom.test.{ts,tsx}`**. Strategy: [erp-test-scale-strategy.md](../../docs/testing/erp-test-scale-strategy.md). **T0 default:** `pnpm test:changed`. Config: [`.config/vitest.config.ts`](../../.config/vitest.config.ts). **ADR-0008** |
| `tests/e2e/` | Playwright `*.spec.ts` | Explicit `goto`/`getByRole`/`getByLabel`; tag stable gates `@smoke`; App Router routes validated here |
| `tests/e2e/utils/` | Browser helpers | Import from `tests/fixtures`; no duplicate magic strings; avoid deep `test.extend` pyramids |

**Playwright playbook (full):** [`docs/testing/e2e-local-playbook.md`](../../docs/testing/e2e-local-playbook.md)

### E0 / E1 / E2 ladder (agents — mandatory)

```txt
E0 preflight (seconds–minutes) → E1 one spec -g filter (1–2 min warm) → E2 pnpm test:e2e only at PR close
```

**Forbidden:** `pnpm test:e2e` after every E2E line change. That rebuilds + runs the whole tree (~8–15+ min).

| Tier | Command | When |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **E0** | `pnpm e2e:preflight:time-clock` (HRM TCI) · future `scripts/e2e-preflight-*.mjs` | Before first Playwright run in a session |
| **E1** | `pnpm exec playwright test <spec> --config .config/playwright.config.ts -g "<fragment>" --workers=1` | After each E2E fix |
| **E2** | `pnpm test:e2e` / `pnpm test:e2e:smoke` | Pre-PR / CI only (human YES) |

Set `$env:PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL='http://127.0.0.1:3001'` when using a warm `next dev -p 3001` (or Playwright `webServer`).

### Base URL and ports

| Port | Role |
| --- | --- |
| **3000** | `pnpm dev` — use for E2E only when `resolveE2EBaseURL()` health probe passes (`tests/e2e/utils/e2e-base-url.ts`) |
| **3001** | Default Playwright harness (`next start` / `webServer`) |
| **3002** | WDK only — **not** App Router E2E |

**Hung 3000:** TCP listen without HTTP → auto-fallback to **3001**. Do not set `PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000` unless auth health responds.

**Cookie / auth env:** `PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL`, `BETTER_AUTH_URL`, and `NEXT_PUBLIC_BETTER_AUTH_URL` must use the **same host** (`localhost` vs `127.0.0.1` breaks cookies). Playwright `webServer` aligns these in `.config/playwright.config.ts`.

### Signed-in specs

- Import `test` / `expect` from `tests/e2e/fixtures/auth.ts` (worker storage state).
- Org activation: `tests/e2e/utils/org-admin-auth.ts` — API sign-in, SQL `activeOrganizationId`, clear `__Secure-neon-auth.local.session_data`, nexus warmup.
- Demo ERP data: `pnpm dev:seed` then `pnpm dev:seed:demo-erp` when specs need `hrm_employee` or portals.

### Route Handler session (401 traps)

For handlers that call `getOrgSessionFromRequest`, prefer **`getOrgSessionFromRequestTrusted`** (`#lib/auth`) when tests or ops set `activeOrganizationId` in DB without refreshing signed `session_data` cache. Example: `lib/features/hrm/time-attendance/time-clock-integration/data/tci-ingest-auth.server.ts`.

### Cookie APIs from Playwright

`page.request` may not carry the live browser cookie jar. For session-cookie ERP POST routes, use **`page.evaluate` + `fetch(..., { credentials: "include" })`** inside the spec (see playbook).

### HRM time clock reference

- Preflight: `pnpm e2e:preflight:time-clock`
- Spec: `tests/e2e/hrm-time-clock-flow.spec.ts`
- Seeds: `tests/e2e/utils/ensure-time-clock-e2e-permissions.ts` (`beforeAll`)

**Workflow DevKit (ADR-0039):** `pnpm dev:stack` — UI **3000**, workflows **3002**. Do **not** run App Router Playwright against **3002**. Do not run Playwright inside `dev:stack` unless you understand shared DB + port isolation.

## Vitest scripts (AGENTS.md §2)

**Pre-push:** when `pnpm gate:push` fails, use **batch-fix** (`.cursor/rules/gate-batch-fix-workflow.mdc`) — do not re-run full L2 after each single test fix.

**Mandatory:** every Vitest invocation must pass `--config .config/vitest.config.ts` (enforced by `pnpm lint:public-lynx-contract` on `package.json` scripts). Bare `pnpm exec vitest run` skips `server-only` / `next/navigation` stubs and produces false failures (e.g. `neon-auth-env.server.test.ts`, Public Lynx tests).

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `pnpm test` | Watch mode (`--config .config/vitest.config.ts`) |
| `pnpm test:fast` | `vitest run --config .config/vitest.config.ts` without coverage (`with-env.mjs`) |
| `pnpm test:ci` / `pnpm test:coverage` | `vitest run --config .config/vitest.config.ts --coverage` |
| `pnpm test:fast:node` / `test:fast:pure` / `test:fast:dom` | Single Vitest project |
| `pnpm test:changed` | **Default edit loop** — git-changed tests only |
| `pnpm artifacts:init` | After clone/pull — `.artifacts/` layout + Vitest blob junction + legacy file migration |
| `pnpm test:local-shards` | Local 4-way shard + merge (high-core Linux/WSL); runs `artifacts:init` first |
| `pnpm test:audit:changed` | Same via audit entry |
| `pnpm test:failures` | Reprint `.artifacts/reports/vitest-failures.txt` without re-running |
| `pnpm test:audit` | Full suite, `--bail=0`, lean digest (JSON deleted on pass) |
| `pnpm test:analyze:imports` | Top slow module imports (console, limit 30) |
| `pnpm test:analyze:imports:report` | Same → `.artifacts/reports/vitest-import-durations.txt` (limit 50) |
| `pnpm test:analyze:imports:warn` | `print=on-warn` (direct Vitest flag) |

Append Vitest path filters after `--`, e.g. `pnpm test:analyze:imports -- tests/unit/planner`.

**Speed ladder:** `test:changed` (seconds) → `test:fast:pure` / `test:fast:node` → `test:fast` / `test:audit` → `test:ci` (coverage; WSL on Windows). **`integrity:behavior`** uses Turbo-cached `test:fast`. Forbidden: Vitest-in-runtime, `/api/test/*` (see erp-test-scale-strategy.md).

**Cache (reruns):** `.artifacts/vitest-vite/` + `experimental.fsModuleCache` on `test:fast`. Second run should be faster. `VITEST_FS_CACHE=0` disables fs cache. `VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=N` caps workers. Details: `docs/testing/vitest-wsl-coverage.md`.

**Partial-log anti-pattern:** Do not debug from Turbo (`errors-only` / `new-only`) or CI blob shards. Run `pnpm test:changed` or `pnpm test:audit`, then `pnpm test:failures` to re-read the digest.

**TypeScript:** Three graphs — `pnpm typecheck` (app) · `pnpm typecheck:test` · `pnpm typecheck:scripts`. Do not add `tests/` to root `tsconfig.json`. See [typescript-compile-efficiency.md](../../docs/testing/typescript-compile-efficiency.md).

## Coverage (V8)

- `pnpm test:ci` / `pnpm test:coverage` → `@vitest/coverage-v8` → `.artifacts/coverage/`.
- **IAM-sensitive** (`lib/auth/**/*.shared.ts`, `lib/auth/callback-path.ts`) → **≥ 95%** coverage enforced.
- **Global executed coverage** ratcheted toward **80%**. Do not enable `coverage.all: true` prematurely.
- Artifacts under `.artifacts/` only (gitignored). Do not commit reports.

